master

etcd-stores all the configurations of the cluster (key value store)
apis server -front end interacts with kube cluster
scheduler- distributes the workload 
controller- makes decision to bring new container 


node - 
we neeed to have more than one node
multiple nodes helps sharing the load 

kubelet - agent (interacts with master)
kubeproxy - to connect the nodes with other nodes
container runtime- container or rocket


kubectl -kubecommand line to manage the cluster

it runs on the agents

kubectl run hello-minikube"
kubectl cluster-info
kubectl get nodes
kubectl get pods 




tasks:
1)application
2)kubernetes cluster


pod is smallest unit in the node and kubernetes cluster
